"{\"uid\": \"smh.com.au-national-mossad-chief-who-led-hunt-to-kill-perpetrators-of-munich-olympic-massacre-dies-at-98-20240103-p5euxv.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"We are sorry, this feature is currently unavailable.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We are working to restore it.\", \"from\": 53, \"to\": 82, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please try again later.\", \"from\": 83, \"to\": 106, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This was published1yearago  Add articles to your saved list and come back to them any time.\", \"from\": 108, \"to\": 199, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Zvi Zamir, who has died aged 98, was a general in the Israel Defence Forces before becoming Director of Mossad, Israel's intelligence agency, in 1968; in this capacity he led Operation Wrath of God to hunt and kill those responsible for theMunich Massacre.\", \"from\": 201, \"to\": 457, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 201, \"end\": 210, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zvi_Zamir\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zvi Zamir\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zvi_Zamir\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zvi_Zamir\"}, {\"begin\": 255, \"end\": 276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Israel Defence Forces\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\"}, {\"begin\": 305, \"end\": 311, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5773273734019943e-77, \"text\": \"Mossad\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\"}, {\"begin\": 313, \"end\": 319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.174512037885936e-38, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}, {\"begin\": 386, \"end\": 391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anger\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.355105899703544e-26, \"text\": \"Wrath\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anger\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anger\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On September 5, 1972, eight heavily armed militants from Black September, a faction of the PLO, stormed the building housing the Israeli delegation to the Munich Olympic Games, killing two athletes and taking nine hostages; they demanded the release of 236 Palestinian prisoners held in Israeli jails.\", \"from\": 459, \"to\": 760, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 550, \"end\": 553, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestine_Liberation_Organization\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.524999640870191e-85, \"text\": \"PLO\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestine_Liberation_Organization\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestine_Liberation_Organization\"}, {\"begin\": 588, \"end\": 595, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2053666224536104e-18, \"text\": \"Israeli\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\"}, {\"begin\": 614, \"end\": 634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1972_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Munich Olympic Games\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1972_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1972_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 716, \"end\": 727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 4.780565661060407e-13, \"text\": \"Palestinian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\"}, {\"begin\": 746, \"end\": 753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2053666224536104e-18, \"text\": \"Israeli\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The government, led by Prime Minister Golda Meir, declined to cave in, and Meir handed responsibility for the crisis to her trusted Mossad chief.\", \"from\": 761, \"to\": 906, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 799, \"end\": 809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Golda_Meir\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Golda Meir\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Golda_Meir\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Golda_Meir\"}, {\"begin\": 893, \"end\": 899, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5773273734019943e-77, \"text\": \"Mossad\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A still of Zamir from the 1999 documentaryOne Day in September, which detailed the events of the 1972 Munich massacre.Credit:Alamy  Zamir rushed to Munich, where he pleaded with West German officials to permit Sayeret Matkal - at that time one of the few military units trained in hostage rescue and counterterrorism - to rescue the Israeli athletes.\", \"from\": 908, \"to\": 1258, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1010, \"end\": 1016, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\", \"score\": 0.9003737378060457, \"rank\": 0.11064989793716677, \"text\": \"Munich\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\"}, {\"begin\": 1056, \"end\": 1062, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\", \"score\": 0.9003737378060457, \"rank\": 0.11064989793716677, \"text\": \"Munich\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\"}, {\"begin\": 1241, \"end\": 1248, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2053666224536104e-18, \"text\": \"Israeli\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But as the German constitution prohibited foreigners from carrying out military operations on German soil, his request was rejected.\", \"from\": 1259, \"to\": 1391, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1270, \"end\": 1289, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Basic_Law_for_the_Federal_Republic_of_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9999979689712453, \"rank\": 2.031033184265457e-06, \"text\": \"German constitution\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Basic_Law_for_the_Federal_Republic_of_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Basic_Law_for_the_Federal_Republic_of_Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 1353, \"end\": 1359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9999922481938804, \"rank\": 7.75185654839888e-06, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The hijackers demanded two helicopters to fly them and their hostages to the nearby F\\u00fcrstenfeldbruck airfield, and a special plane to take them from there to an Arab country.\", \"from\": 1393, \"to\": 1567, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1554, \"end\": 1558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.809565172680818e-17, \"text\": \"Arab\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Germans agreed and planned to use snipers to shoot the hijackers when they transferred from the helicopters to the plane.\", \"from\": 1568, \"to\": 1693, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1572, \"end\": 1579, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9999883477272705, \"rank\": 1.1652404372361668e-05, \"text\": \"Germans\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Zamir, who was flown to F\\u00fcrstenfeldbruck just ahead of the terrorists and their hostages, watched with growing frustration as the Germans prepared themselves for the showdown.\", \"from\": 1695, \"to\": 1870, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1719, \"end\": 1735, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/F\\u00fcrstenfeldbruck\", \"score\": 0.9255849604882891, \"rank\": 0.06460625109127516, \"text\": \"F\\u00fcrstenfeldbruck\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/F\\u00fcrstenfeldbruck\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/F\\u00fcrstenfeldbruck\"}, {\"begin\": 1825, \"end\": 1832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9999883477272705, \"rank\": 1.1652404372361668e-05, \"text\": \"Germans\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The Germans were useless \\u2026 useless all the way,\\\" he recalled.\", \"from\": 1871, \"to\": 1933, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1876, \"end\": 1883, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9999883477272705, \"rank\": 1.1652404372361668e-05, \"text\": \"Germans\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was pitch black at the airport, and the artificial light was patently inadequate for a sniping operation.\", \"from\": 1935, \"to\": 2043, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Worse, only five snipers were allocated the task of tackling eight terrorists; several of the snipers' guns were not fitted with telescopic sights, and the snipers, deployed approximately 100 metres away from their commanders, were not issued with means of communication to co-ordinate their firing.\", \"from\": 2044, \"to\": 2343, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A Palestinian terrorist holds members of the Israeli Olympic team hostage at their quarters at the Munich athletes' village in 1972.Credit:AP  When the snipers opened fire they failed to kill all the hijackers in the first volley and a gunfight ensued.\", \"from\": 2345, \"to\": 2597, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2347, \"end\": 2358, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 4.780565661060407e-13, \"text\": \"Palestinian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\"}, {\"begin\": 2390, \"end\": 2410, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_at_the_1972_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Israeli Olympic team\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_at_the_1972_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_at_the_1972_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2444, \"end\": 2450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\", \"score\": 0.9003737378060457, \"rank\": 0.11064989793716677, \"text\": \"Munich\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The three remaining terrorists tossed hand grenades into one of the helicopters; the explosion ignited the fuel tank and the handcuffed Israelis still sitting inside were burnt alive.\", \"from\": 2598, \"to\": 2781, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2734, \"end\": 2742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2725392810398278e-26, \"text\": \"Israelis\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another hijacker sprayed the Israelis in the other helicopter with bullets.\", \"from\": 2782, \"to\": 2857, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2811, \"end\": 2819, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2725392810398278e-26, \"text\": \"Israelis\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Zamir, witnessing the disaster from the control tower, insisted on getting out to the balcony to negotiate with the terrorists.\", \"from\": 2859, \"to\": 2986, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Taking with him an Arabic-speaking aide, Zamir used a megaphone to shout: \\\"Stop firing \\u2026 the plane is ready for you \\u2026 STOP FIRING\\\".\", \"from\": 2987, \"to\": 3118, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But, as he recalled, \\\"Their reply was clear \\u2026 they opened fire at us on the balcony.\\\"\", \"from\": 3119, \"to\": 3204, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Back at the Olympic Village, Zamir telephoned Meir at home in Israel.\", \"from\": 3206, \"to\": 3275, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3268, \"end\": 3274, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.174512037885936e-38, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Golda, I have got bad news,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 3276, \"to\": 3314, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am just back from the airport \\u2026 not one of the Israelis has survived.\\\"\", \"from\": 3315, \"to\": 3388, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3365, \"end\": 3373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2725392810398278e-26, \"text\": \"Israelis\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a later interview, Zamir said: \\\"To see this happen on German soil was a terrible sight.\\\"\", \"from\": 3389, \"to\": 3480, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3446, \"end\": 3452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.9999922481938804, \"rank\": 7.75185654839888e-06, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The aftermath of the events at F\\u00fcrstenfeldbruck airfield in 1972,Credit:Fairfax archive  Zvi Zamir was born Zvicka Zarzevsky on March 3, 1925 in Poland.\", \"from\": 3482, \"to\": 3634, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3571, \"end\": 3580, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zvi_Zamir\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Zvi Zamir\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zvi_Zamir\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zvi_Zamir\"}, {\"begin\": 3627, \"end\": 3633, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Second_Polish_Republic\", \"score\": 0.8837741400440483, \"rank\": 0.1312092151472292, \"text\": \"Poland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Second_Polish_Republic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Second_Polish_Republic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When he was seven months old, the Zarzevskys settled in Palestine, then under British Mandate.\", \"from\": 3635, \"to\": 3729, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3691, \"end\": 3700, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mandatory_Palestine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1514969220734484e-23, \"text\": \"Palestine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mandatory_Palestine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mandatory_Palestine\"}, {\"begin\": 3713, \"end\": 3728, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mandatory_Palestine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6800765828334174e-30, \"text\": \"British Mandate\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mandatory_Palestine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mandatory_Palestine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1942, he joined the Palmach, the elite strike force of the Haganah, the clandestine military organisation of the Jewish community in Palestine.\", \"from\": 3731, \"to\": 3877, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3754, \"end\": 3761, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palmach\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Palmach\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palmach\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palmach\"}, {\"begin\": 3793, \"end\": 3800, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haganah\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Haganah\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haganah\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Haganah\"}, {\"begin\": 3847, \"end\": 3853, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jews\", \"score\": 0.9999999999654392, \"rank\": 3.275021767199341e-11, \"text\": \"Jewish\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jews\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jews\"}, {\"begin\": 3867, \"end\": 3876, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mandatory_Palestine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1514969220734484e-23, \"text\": \"Palestine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mandatory_Palestine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mandatory_Palestine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1946, the British arrested Zamir for his involvement in bringing illegal immigrants to Palestine and imprisoned him at the Latrun jail.\", \"from\": 3878, \"to\": 4016, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3891, \"end\": 3898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Army\", \"score\": 0.8371588790848012, \"rank\": 0.19451456824097973, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Army\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Army\"}, {\"begin\": 3968, \"end\": 3977, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mandatory_Palestine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1514969220734484e-23, \"text\": \"Palestine\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mandatory_Palestine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mandatory_Palestine\"}, {\"begin\": 4004, \"end\": 4010, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latrun\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.579152643219597e-89, \"text\": \"Latrun\", \"types\": [\"Q532\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latrun\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Latrun\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On his release a year later, he was made commander of the 6th Palmach battalion and took part in battles against Arabs in and around Jerusalem during the War of Independence.\", \"from\": 4017, \"to\": 4191, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4130, \"end\": 4135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arabs\", \"score\": 0.9999999982319423, \"rank\": 1.7681112208499343e-09, \"text\": \"Arabs\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arabs\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Arabs\"}, {\"begin\": 4150, \"end\": 4159, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jerusalem\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.964541541540186e-37, \"text\": \"Jerusalem\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jerusalem\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jerusalem\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1950 Zamir was made commander of the Givati Brigade, and in 1953 he attended the Staff College, Camberley in England.\", \"from\": 4193, \"to\": 4313, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4233, \"end\": 4247, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Givati_Brigade\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Givati Brigade\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Givati_Brigade\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Givati_Brigade\"}, {\"begin\": 4277, \"end\": 4301, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Staff_College,_Camberley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Staff College, Camberley\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Staff_College,_Camberley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Staff_College,_Camberley\"}, {\"begin\": 4277, \"end\": 4301, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Staff_College,_Camberley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Staff College, Camberley\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Staff_College,_Camberley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Staff_College,_Camberley\"}, {\"begin\": 4305, \"end\": 4312, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\", \"score\": 0.9971418275621177, \"rank\": 0.002865576507573298, \"text\": \"England\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_England\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On his return to Israel, he was appointed commander of the infantry school, and during the 1956 Sinai campaign he served as a brigade commander.\", \"from\": 4314, \"to\": 4458, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4331, \"end\": 4337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.174512037885936e-38, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}, {\"begin\": 4405, \"end\": 4424, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suez_Crisis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"1956 Sinai campaign\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suez_Crisis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Suez_Crisis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1957, he took leave and enrolled as a student of geography at the Hebrew University of Jerusalem.\", \"from\": 4460, \"to\": 4560, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Upon completing his studies he was promoted to brigadier, and after a stint as IDF's training branch commander, in 1962 he was made OC Southern Command in charge of the Israeli-Egyptian front, which during his tenure was relatively quiet.\", \"from\": 4561, \"to\": 4799, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4640, \"end\": 4643, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.96087719343829e-22, \"text\": \"IDF\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\"}, {\"begin\": 4693, \"end\": 4695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pepper_spray\", \"score\": 0.99999937015238, \"rank\": 6.298479901385146e-07, \"text\": \"OC\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pepper_spray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pepper_spray\"}, {\"begin\": 4696, \"end\": 4712, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Southern_Command\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.881553693112177e-51, \"text\": \"Southern Command\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Southern_Command\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Southern_Command\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On July 15, 1966, Zamir was appointed military attache in London, which meant that he missed theJune 1967 Six Day War.\", \"from\": 4800, \"to\": 4918, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4858, \"end\": 4864, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999996935003, \"rank\": 3.050727321672971e-10, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Zamir in 1966.Credit:Alamy  Zamir's appointment to head the Mossad surprised many, and it took him two years before he began to feel and understand the real dimensions of his job.\", \"from\": 4920, \"to\": 5099, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4980, \"end\": 4986, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5773273734019943e-77, \"text\": \"Mossad\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As director, Zamir had a hands-on style of leadership.\", \"from\": 5100, \"to\": 5154, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His reports were voluminous; he never concealed anything from the government and he took responsibility for both successes and failures, typically taking the latter much to heart.\", \"from\": 5155, \"to\": 5334, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meir would often console him with the words: \\\"When trees are felled, the chips will fly.\\\"\", \"from\": 5335, \"to\": 5424, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After Munich, as Zamir recalled, \\\"Golda wanted very much, that the terrorists [responsible for Munich] will be brought to trial.\", \"from\": 5426, \"to\": 5554, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5432, \"end\": 5438, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\", \"score\": 0.9003737378060457, \"rank\": 0.11064989793716677, \"text\": \"Munich\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\"}, {\"begin\": 5521, \"end\": 5527, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\", \"score\": 0.9003737378060457, \"rank\": 0.11064989793716677, \"text\": \"Munich\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But she realised that this is impossible.\\\"\", \"from\": 5555, \"to\": 5597, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, Zamir asked her for permission to kill them.\", \"from\": 5598, \"to\": 5651, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She instructed him to draw up a list of targets: they did not have to be involved in Munich or even be members of Black September to make the cut, as the objective was to wipe out the entire terrorist network in Europe.\", \"from\": 5653, \"to\": 5872, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5738, \"end\": 5744, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\", \"score\": 0.9003737378060457, \"rank\": 0.11064989793716677, \"text\": \"Munich\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A special secret committee, \\\"Committee X\\\", chaired by the prime minister, went through Zamir's list and approved what became known as Operation Wrath of God.\", \"from\": 5873, \"to\": 6030, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6017, \"end\": 6022, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anger\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.355105899703544e-26, \"text\": \"Wrath\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anger\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anger\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first to die was Abdel Wael Zwaiter, officially a translator at the Libyan Embassy in Italy, but, according to Mossad, a Black September terrorist - he was shot 12 times by Zamir's hit team on October 16, 1972 in Rome.\", \"from\": 6032, \"to\": 6254, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6059, \"end\": 6071, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abdel_Wael_Zwaiter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Wael Zwaiter\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abdel_Wael_Zwaiter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Abdel_Wael_Zwaiter\"}, {\"begin\": 6122, \"end\": 6127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Italy\", \"score\": 0.9999635735134531, \"rank\": 3.6427813668042166e-05, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Italy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Italy\"}, {\"begin\": 6147, \"end\": 6153, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5773273734019943e-77, \"text\": \"Mossad\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\"}, {\"begin\": 6249, \"end\": 6253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"score\": 0.9956446704544003, \"rank\": 0.004374372203454631, \"text\": \"Rome\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Zamir would often fly to Europe to supervise operations and be with his people.\", \"from\": 6256, \"to\": 6335, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I spoke to [the hit team] before the mission, during the mission and afterwards too, and I knew them all,\\\" he said in an interview.\", \"from\": 6336, \"to\": 6468, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not all went well.\", \"from\": 6470, \"to\": 6488, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On July 21, 1973, Zamir's assassins, tracking a man they believed to be the mastermind of Munich, Ali Hassan Salameh, killed an innocent Moroccan waiter in the town of Lillehammer in Norway.\", \"from\": 6489, \"to\": 6679, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6579, \"end\": 6585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\", \"score\": 0.9003737378060457, \"rank\": 0.11064989793716677, \"text\": \"Munich\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\"}, {\"begin\": 6587, \"end\": 6605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ali_Hassan_Salameh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ali Hassan Salameh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ali_Hassan_Salameh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ali_Hassan_Salameh\"}, {\"begin\": 6626, \"end\": 6634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"score\": 0.9976633025111147, \"rank\": 0.0023421688391649913, \"text\": \"Moroccan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\"}, {\"begin\": 6657, \"end\": 6668, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lillehammer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.418384612861359e-21, \"text\": \"Lillehammer\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lillehammer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lillehammer\"}, {\"begin\": 6672, \"end\": 6678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norwegian_campaign\", \"score\": 0.999999649136105, \"rank\": 3.5086437034923447e-07, \"text\": \"Norway\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norwegian_campaign\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norwegian_campaign\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Norwegian police managed to apprehend six of the back-up team, interrogated them and put them on trial.\", \"from\": 6680, \"to\": 6783, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6680, \"end\": 6689, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norwegian_Army\", \"score\": 0.999998023284341, \"rank\": 1.976531869825385e-06, \"text\": \"Norwegian\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norwegian_Army\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norwegian_Army\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Lillehammer Affair was an embarrassing failure and Zamir accepted full responsibility, but when he offered his resignation, Meir asked him to stay on: her trust in him was absolute.\", \"from\": 6785, \"to\": 6970, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Over a period of 20 years, even after Zamir's retirement from the Mossad, Israeli agents continued executing Wrath of God, killing dozens of Palestinians, including two of the three terrorists who survived Munich.\", \"from\": 6971, \"to\": 7184, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7037, \"end\": 7043, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5773273734019943e-77, \"text\": \"Mossad\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\"}, {\"begin\": 7045, \"end\": 7052, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2053666224536104e-18, \"text\": \"Israeli\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\"}, {\"begin\": 7112, \"end\": 7124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.633904545112164e-25, \"text\": \"Palestinians\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\"}, {\"begin\": 7177, \"end\": 7183, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\", \"score\": 0.9003737378060457, \"rank\": 0.11064989793716677, \"text\": \"Munich\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Munich_Agreement\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This campaign was depicted in Steven Spielberg's 2005 filmMunich, which Zamir hated, describing it as a \\\"cowboy movie\\\" and a \\\"fairytale \\u2026 based on the director's fertile imagination\\\".\", \"from\": 7186, \"to\": 7369, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was played by the Israeli actor Ami Weinberg.\", \"from\": 7370, \"to\": 7418, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7391, \"end\": 7398, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.2053666224536104e-18, \"text\": \"Israeli\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel_Defense_Forces\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In October 1973, Zamir's attention shifted to preparations by Egypt and Syria to attack Israel.\", \"from\": 7420, \"to\": 7515, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7482, \"end\": 7487, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"score\": 0.9999999978690539, \"rank\": 2.1305062389246856e-09, \"text\": \"Egypt\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\"}, {\"begin\": 7492, \"end\": 7497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syria\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4566426707104007e-18, \"text\": \"Syria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Syria\"}, {\"begin\": 7508, \"end\": 7514, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.174512037885936e-38, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While military intelligence dismissed Arab mobilisation as a false alarm, Zamir - typically - took the threat seriously and warned of the possibility of all-out war.\", \"from\": 7516, \"to\": 7681, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7554, \"end\": 7558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.809565172680818e-17, \"text\": \"Arab\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In London on October 5, Zamir met Israel's most senior spy, Ashraf Marwan, the son-in-law of the former Egyptian president Gamal Abdel Nasser.\", \"from\": 7683, \"to\": 7825, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7686, \"end\": 7692, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999996935003, \"rank\": 3.050727321672971e-10, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 7717, \"end\": 7723, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.174512037885936e-38, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}, {\"begin\": 7743, \"end\": 7756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashraf_Marwan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ashraf Marwan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashraf_Marwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashraf_Marwan\"}, {\"begin\": 7787, \"end\": 7795, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.946428699268891e-15, \"text\": \"Egyptian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt\"}, {\"begin\": 7806, \"end\": 7824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gamal_Abdel_Nasser\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2947001603437927e-16, \"text\": \"Gamal Abdel Nasser\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gamal_Abdel_Nasser\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gamal_Abdel_Nasser\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Marwan warned Zamir that \\\"war would break out tomorrow\\\" and provided him with maps and documents.\", \"from\": 7826, \"to\": 7923, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7826, \"end\": 7832, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marwan_I\", \"score\": 0.9999910024748769, \"rank\": 8.997606163189586e-06, \"text\": \"Marwan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marwan_I\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marwan_I\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This was too short a timescale to enable Israel to fully mobilise her forces, but it did provide the Israelis with some extra time to take measures to contain the imminent Arab attack.\", \"from\": 7924, \"to\": 8108, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7965, \"end\": 7971, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.174512037885936e-38, \"text\": \"Israel\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israel\"}, {\"begin\": 8025, \"end\": 8033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2725392810398278e-26, \"text\": \"Israelis\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Israelis\"}, {\"begin\": 8096, \"end\": 8100, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.809565172680818e-17, \"text\": \"Arab\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Palestinians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Agranat Commission of inquiry into the circumstances leading to the outbreak of the Yom Kippur War praised Zamir for bringing the message from London.\", \"from\": 8110, \"to\": 8264, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8114, \"end\": 8132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agranat_Commission\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Agranat Commission\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agranat_Commission\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agranat_Commission\"}, {\"begin\": 8198, \"end\": 8212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yom_Kippur_War\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Yom Kippur War\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yom_Kippur_War\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yom_Kippur_War\"}, {\"begin\": 8257, \"end\": 8263, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999996935003, \"rank\": 3.050727321672971e-10, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Zamir later said: \\\"The greatest achievement of Mossad during my time in charge was to provide the warning about the looming war.\\\"\", \"from\": 8265, \"to\": 8394, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8312, \"end\": 8318, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.5773273734019943e-77, \"text\": \"Mossad\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mossad\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When he retired in 1978, Zamir became director-general and chairman of National Oil Refineries, a post he held for 15 years.\", \"from\": 8396, \"to\": 8520, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8467, \"end\": 8490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Neath_(1922)_F.C.\", \"score\": 0.9999999898154783, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"National Oil Refineries\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\"